#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn11.7"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn11.7:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 11 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 11 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.7:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga "
msgstr "1. The First Chapter "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn11.7:0.3"
msgid "7. Nadubbhiyasutta "
msgstr "7. Not Betray "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.485, sc1
msgctxt "sn11.7:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.7:1.2"
msgid "“Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, sakkassa devānamindassa rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso parivitakko udapādi: "
msgstr "“Once upon a time, mendicants, as Sakka, lord of gods, was in private retreat this thought came to his mind, "

# NOTE: BB’s “Transgress against” seems vague and weak, especially when referring to someone you’re in constant war against. The root is the same as mittadduno.
msgctxt "sn11.7:1.3"
msgid "‘yopi me assa supaccatthiko tassapāhaṃ na dubbheyyan’ti. "
msgstr "‘I should never betray even a sworn enemy.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.7:1.4"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vepacitti asurindo sakkassa devānamindassa cetasā cetoparivitakkamaññāya yena sakko devānamindo tenupasaṅkami. "
msgstr "And then Vepacitti, lord of demons, knowing what Sakka was thinking, approached him. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.7:1.5"
msgid "Addasā kho, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo vepacittiṃ asurindaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ. "
msgstr "Sakka saw Vepacitti coming off in the distance, "

msgctxt "sn11.7:1.6"
msgid "Disvāna vepacittiṃ asurindaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "and said to him, "

msgctxt "sn11.7:1.7"
msgid "‘tiṭṭha, vepacitti, gahitosī’ti. "
msgstr "‘Stop, Vepacitti, you’re caught!’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
#. VAR: tadeva tvaṃ mā pajahāsī’ti → tadeva tvaṃ mārisa pahāsīti (bj) | tadeva tvaṃ mārisa jahāsīti (s1-3, km) | tad eva tvam mā pahāsīti (pts1)
msgctxt "sn11.7:2.1"
msgid "‘Yadeva te, mārisa, pubbe cittaṃ, tadeva tvaṃ mā pajahāsī’ti. "
msgstr "‘Dear sir, don’t give up the idea you just had!’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
#. VAR: adubbhāyā’ti → adrubbhāya (mr)
msgctxt "sn11.7:3.1"
msgid "‘Sapassu ca me, vepacitti, adubbhāyā’ti. "
msgstr "‘Swear, Vepacitti, that you won’t betray me.’ "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn11.7:4.1"
msgid "‘Yaṃ musā bhaṇato pāpaṃ, "
msgstr "‘Whatever bad things happen to a liar, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.7:4.2"
msgid "Yaṃ pāpaṃ ariyūpavādino; "
msgstr "or to someone who slanders the noble ones, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.7:4.3"
msgid "Mittadduno ca yaṃ pāpaṃ, "
msgstr "or to someone who betrays a friend, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.7:4.4"
msgid "Yaṃ pāpaṃ akataññuno; "
msgstr "or to someone who’s ungrateful, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: phusatu → phusati (bj, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn11.7:4.5"
msgid "Tameva pāpaṃ phusatu, "
msgstr "the same bad things impact "

# NOTE: Vepacitti is reminding Sakka of their family connection.
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.7:4.6"
msgid "Yo te dubbhe sujampatī’”ti. "
msgstr "anyone who betrays you, Sujā’s husband.’”"

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
